		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: A memory leak flaw was found in the glutAddSubMenu function of freeglut, an open-source alternative to the OpenGL Utility Toolkit. This flaw allows an attacker to launch a denial of service attack by crashing or hanging the program or taking advantage of other unexpected program behavior resulting from a low memory condition. \n            STATEMENT: The flaw allows an attacker to potentially cause a denial of service attack by crashing a program, but the impact is minimal.",
